			<cite>Matt said on : </cite>
<small class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-12018" title="">August 29th, 2008 at 9:14 pm</a> </small>
						<br />



<p>It is valuable to back up the two files WPA.DBL and WPA.BAK from the Windows\System32 folder.Then, should they get damaged, or should you do a ‘Repair’ reinstallation of Win XP, these files can be copied back to restore the prior activation status. </p>
<p>However, this only works in those limited circumstances. The contents of these two files is matched to the specific Windows setup; therefore, contrary to what many journalists and members of the user community have written in recent months, restoring these files will not restore your activation status following a reformat and clean install.</p>
		</li><br />

	        
        	             
